<!DOCTYPE task PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Task//EN" "task.dtd" []>
<task xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="specifying-default-location-for-new-documents" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:task.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Specifying Default Location for New Documents</title>
  <taskbody id="body">
    <context>
      <p>When you create a new document and save it, it is saved by default to a particular location.</p>
      <p>On Windows, you can specify the default directory for saving new documents.<note>
          <p>There is no such option on Linux and Mac OS X.</p>
        </note></p>
    </context>
    <steps>
      <step>
        <cmd>Call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <p>To call up the <keyword>Preferences Dialog</keyword>, choose <menucascade>
              <uicontrol>Tools</uicontrol>
              <uicontrol>Preferences</uicontrol>
            </menucascade>.</p>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Select the <keyword>General tab</keyword>.</cmd>
        <info>
          <fig>
            <title>General tab.</title>
            <image href="preferences-dialog-general-tab-documents-location.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
          </fig>
        </info>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>To specify the default location for new documents, do the following: </cmd>
        <substeps>
          <substep>
            <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Browse</uicontrol> button next to the <uicontrol>Documents location</uicontrol> field.</cmd>
          </substep>
          <substep>
            <cmd>In the <keyword>Browse For Folder Dialog</keyword>, select a directory and click <uicontrol>OK</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info>
              <note>
                <p>To create a new directory, click the <uicontrol>Make New Folder</uicontrol> button.</p>
              </note>
            </info>
            <info>
              <fig>
                <title>Browse For Folder Dialog.</title>
                <image href="browse-for-folder-dialog.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
              </fig>
            </info>
          </substep>
        </substeps>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Apply</uicontrol> button to apply the settings.</cmd>
      </step>
      <step>
        <cmd>Click the <uicontrol>Close</uicontrol> button to close the dialog.</cmd>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
</task>
